						<b>Gangjeong & Sanja (fried rice cookies)</b><br><br>
						Glutinous rice is kneaded with bean water, steamed, pounded in a mortar, and kneaded again with a rolling pin several times. Then, it is flattened with a rolling pin, dried, and deep fat fried. </td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="10" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr>
						<td>
							It is coated with seban (crushed powder of dried steamed rice), maehwa (fried sweet rice shaped like Japanese apricot blossoms), pine pollen (or pine flower), and sesame seeds. It is served as dessert.
						</td>
					</tr>	
