					<tr valign="top">
						<td width="15">1)</td>
						<td>Soak glutinous rice in water for 15 days to ferment.</td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="7" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td>2)</td>
						<td>Grind soaked beans to make thin bean water.</td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="7" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td>3)</td>
						<td>Grind glutinous rice in 1) and knead with bean water and refined rice wine, and steam.</td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="7" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td>4)</td>
						<td>Steamed rice is pounded in a mortar and poured on flour spreaded on a flat surface. Roll with rolling pin and if almost dried and hard, then make shapes and let dry.</td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="7" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td>5)</td>
						<td>Well-dried 'sanja' is dipped in warm oil and being risen in hot oil.</td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="7" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td>6)</td>
						<td>Drain oils from fried 'sanja' and coat them with honey and other coatings.</td>
